Source: hermes
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Maintainer: EmbedSquare <ops@embedsquare.com>
# We deliberately keep Build-Depends minimal. dh-python and python3-all
# would trigger dh-python's auto-detection of pyproject.toml and try to
# build a wheel at .deb build time — we skip that with --without python3
# in debian/rules. nodejs/npm/pnpm are handled in the workflow's "Install
# build deps" step (system apt's nodejs is too old for SvelteKit).
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/Rushikesh-Palande/hermes

Package: hermes
# Architecture: all — the package is pure Python source + a JS bundle.
# The platform-specific Python venv is built at install time by
# packaging/install.sh (postinst) so wheels match the host's libc/glibc.
Architecture: all
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         python3.11,
         python3-venv,
         postgresql-16,
         timescaledb-2-postgresql-16,
         mosquitto,
         nginx,
         adduser
Recommends: certbot, python3-certbot-nginx
Description: HERMES — industrial sensor monitoring + event detection
 HERMES ingests 12-channel ADC telemetry from STM32 hardware over MQTT
 at ~100 Hz per sensor, runs four parallel event-detection algorithms
 (A/B/C/D + BREAK mode transition), persists events with +-9 s context
 windows, and presents live and historical data through a SvelteKit
 dashboard.
 .
 The package installs HERMES under /opt/hermes/, creates a `hermes`
 system user, sets up a Postgres role and database, installs systemd
 units (hermes-api.service + hermes-ingest.service), and configures
 nginx as a reverse proxy. After install:
 .
   * UI:   http://<host>/
   * API:  http://<host>:8080/api/health
   * Logs: journalctl -u hermes-api -u hermes-ingest -f
 .
 Designed for continuous unattended operation on a Raspberry Pi 4 in
 industrial environments. See /opt/hermes/docs/operations/ for the
 ops runbook.
